11. Results
The designed PCB successfully integrates sensor acquisition, display control, wireless communication, and industrial power management into a single platform. The board demonstrates stable operation, reliable sensor interfacing, and effective wireless data transmission, making it suitable for IoT and automation applications.
12. Conclusion
The PIC18F-Based IoT Development Board provides a comprehensive hardware solution for embedded and IoT applications. By integrating analog signal conditioning, wireless communication, display interfaces, and industrial-grade power support, the system offers a flexible platform for monitoring and control applications. The design reduces hardware complexity while improving scalability and ease of development, making it suitable for educational, research, and industrial environments.
